      <body>If you select Buenos Aires as timezone right now, the offset used is -7200, i had to monkey patch this on my apps to show the valid offset when returning tz 'Buenos Aires'.

The offset has been changed a couple of weeks ago and as i said it will be -0200 until March 2009.


Check this out:

@@@ ruby
&gt;&gt; Time.now.in_time_zone 'Buenos Aires'
=&gt; Thu, 13 Nov 2008 12:40:48 ARST -02:00
@@@</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you select Buenos Aires as timezone right now, the offset
used is -7200, i had to monkey patch this on my apps to show the
valid offset when returning tz 'Buenos Aires'.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The offset has been changed a couple of weeks ago and as i said
it will be -0200 until March 2009.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check this out:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Time.now.in_time_zone 'Buenos Aires'
=&amp;gt; Thu, 13 Nov 2008 12:40:48 ARST -02:00
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
