      <body>That's because Buenos Aires is observing daylight savings time:

@@@ ruby
&gt;&gt; Time.zone = 'Buenos Aires'
=&gt; &quot;Buenos Aires&quot;
&gt;&gt; Time.zone.now
=&gt; Thu, 13 Nov 2008 13:08:59 ARST -02:00
&gt;&gt; Time.zone.now.dst?
=&gt; true
&gt;&gt; t2 = Time.zone.now + 6.months
=&gt; Wed, 13 May 2009 13:09:20 ART -03:00
&gt;&gt; t2.dst?
=&gt; false
@@@

The #utc_offset of a TimeZone is fixed to the non-dst offset, so that it will appear consistently in the time zone select menu.

For example: US Central time will always appear in the time zone select as:

&quot;(GMT-06:00) Central Time (US &amp; Canada)&quot;

whether or not it's currently dst.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;That's because Buenos Aires is observing daylight savings
time:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Time.zone = 'Buenos Aires'
=&amp;gt; &amp;quot;Buenos Aires&amp;quot;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Time.zone.now
=&amp;gt; Thu, 13 Nov 2008 13:08:59 ARST -02:00
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Time.zone.now.dst?
=&amp;gt; true
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; t2 = Time.zone.now + 6.months
=&amp;gt; Wed, 13 May 2009 13:09:20 ART -03:00
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; t2.dst?
=&amp;gt; false
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The #utc_offset of a TimeZone is fixed to the non-dst offset, so
that it will appear consistently in the time zone select menu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example: US Central time will always appear in the time zone
select as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;(GMT-06:00) Central Time (US &amp;amp; Canada)&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;whether or not it's currently dst.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
